                <note rend="inline" type="source">No. 4.</note>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Received at Washington August 22.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Jay</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Fish</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1870-08-21">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">August</hi> 21, 1870.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Fish,</hi>
                    <hi rend="italic">Secretary, Washington:</hi>
                </p>
                <p>England, Italy, and Russia have mutually agreed to rest neutral, and not to
                    change their position without notice and statement of reasons. Austria, asked to
                    join neutral league, will consent with the additional understanding that efforts
                    for mediation shall be made, not separately but jointly.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>JAY.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
